Riyadh: The Saudi national football team are gearing up for friendly matches against Venezuela and Bolivia in the coastal city of Jeddah in March. For the latest updates, follow us on Twitter @ArabNewsSport The matches are the next stage in the Green Falcons’ preparatory program for March. The national team’s management announced the establishment of a preparatory camp in the city for squad members from March 20-28. The first match will be on March 24 against Venezuela, and the second against Bolivia on March 28. Both matches will be held at Prince Abdullah Al-Faisal Stadium.